DAVIDSON, N.C. (AP) _ Curtiss-Wright Corp. (CW) on Wednesday reported fourth-quarter profit of $76.6 million.On a per-share basis, the Davidson, North Carolina-based company said it had profit of $1.94. Earnings, adjusted for non-recurring costs, were $2.40 per share.The results exceeded Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of four analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of $2.36 per share.The engineering firm posted revenue of $666.8 million in the period. Its adjusted revenue was $655.3 million, missing Street forecasts. Three analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $680 million.For the year, the company reported profit of $267.2 million, or $6.58 per share. Revenue was reported as $2.51 billion.Curtiss-Wright expects full-year earnings in the range of $8.05 to $8.25 per share, with revenue in the range of $2.53 billion to $2.58 billion._____This story was generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on CW at https://www.zacks.com/ap/CW